Peru 1998

Primera División

Note: an Apertura and a Clausura championship was played; the winners
are qualified for the Copa Libertadores and play off for the 1998 title.
If the same team would have won both tournaments, it would have been 
the champion and the two runners-up would have played off for the
second Copa Libertadores place.

The team with the worst record in Apertura and Clausura together was relegated;
the one but last team in this table played off against the winners of the
Segunda División (the winners of the Copa Perú were promoted automatically).

